# Load GS Data to HDFS
Since the wdi_gs table points to a GS location, data must be transferred from GS to Hadoop cluster when running a query. It would be more efficient if the data is stored in the HDFS.
- Create a hive table `wdi_csv_text` that points to an empty HDFS directory
- Import data from `wdi_gs` to `wdi_csv_text`

msg.data:
Load GS Data to HDFS

Since the wdi_gs table points to a GS location, data must be transferred from GS to Hadoop cluster when running a query. It would be more efficient if the data is stored in the HDFS.

  • Create a hive table wdi_csv_text that points to an empty HDFS directory
  • Import data from wdi_gs to wdi_csv_text

paragraphs.text: DROP TABLE IF EXISTS wdi_csv_text

paragraphs.title: Create wdi_csv_text table
paragraphs.text:
CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE wdi_csv_text
(year INTEGER, countryName STRING, countryCode STRING, indicatorName STRING, indicatorCode STRING, indicatorValue FLOAT)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED FIELDS TERMINATED BY ',' LINES TERMINATED BY '\n'
LOCATION 'hdfs:///user/kunjpatel/hive/wdi/wdi_csv_text'

paragraphs.title: Insert data from wdi_gs to wdi_csv_text
paragraphs.text:
INSERT OVERWRITE TABLE wdi_csv_text
SELECT 
    *
FROM wdi_gs

    t2.year AS year

FROM (SELECT
        MAX(indicatorValue) AS indicatorVal
        , countryname
      FROM wdi_csv_parquet

      AND indicatorValue <> 0
      GROUP BY countryname ) t1
 INNER JOIN wdi_csv_parquet t2
 ON t1.indicatorVal = t2.indicatorValue
 AND t1.countryName = t2.countryName
